The paper proposes a method to incorporate semantic features into network embeddings by matching important words between text sequences for all pairs of vertices. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of natural language processing (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper evaluates the proposed framework on three real-world benchmarks for downstream tasks, including link prediction and multi-label vertex classification, which are common tasks in machine learning and data mining (cs.SI, cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of aggregation functions, which are commonly used in information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.AI).
